About
Located in the most emblematic street of Barcelona, Las Ramblas, we find the New Wax Museum of Barcelona. A completely renovated project, both conceptually and in terms of figures, where emblematic characters and the latest technology are combined to make you live an unforgettable experience. An experience in which you will find 28 sets, including The Money Heist, Star Wars, Hall of fame, Pop stars, among which are more than 130 classic characters such as Don Quixote or Picasso, or as contemporary as Rosalia, Messi or Billie Eillish Don't forget our last stop, El Bosc de les Fades, the emblematic bar set in an enchanted forest, an authentic oasis in the middle of the city.
Duration: 1-2 hours

The area

Address
Neighborhood: Barrio Gòtico (Barri Gòtic)
With its iconic, old-Europe streets and alleys, this picturesque neighborhood is the very heart of Barcelona. It blends historic artifacts from its days under Roman dominion up through the Spanish Civil War with a vibrant modern-day culture of artisan shops and authentic culinary experiences. Avid explorers will be thrilled to discover quaint terraces and plazas brought to life by the many small bars and local musicians lasting late into the night. Fashionistas will be drawn to Portal de L’Angel, which is lined with well-known brand names and smaller boutique stands.
How to get there
  • Drassanes • 3 min walk
  • Liceu • 8 min walk

Well done celebrity wax figures and displays!
Oct 2024 • Couples
Having been to several Madame Tussaud's wax museums as well as some really lame ones, I didn't have high expectations. I was pleasantly surprised at the quality of the displays and the experience-based features. While there are a lot of Spanish characters I wasn't real familiar with, the majority were world renowned celebrities, some living and some not. There are some newer characters (Taylor Swift, Game of Thrones, Star Wars Rey, etc) as well as classic characters. This was of the same quality as the Madame Tussaud's we've seen and I'd recommend a visit.

Amazing experience!
Oct 2024 • Family
We recently visited the Museum of Wax in Barcelona, and we had an amazing time! The wax figures were incredibly lifelike, and it felt like we were rubbing shoulders with some of the biggest celebrities and historical figures. We had so much fun posing for photos with famous personalities-from actors and musicians to world leaders. The kids especially enjoyed taking selfies with their favorite stars, and we all shared lots of laughs recreating iconic scenes. The museum was well-organized, and the staff were friendly, adding to the overall enjoyable experience. It was a perfect family outing, and we left with fantastic memories and loads of photos!
